What you need to know:  Starting the day four shots behind junior amateur Njoroge Kibugu, Chinhoi’s putter seemed to be better than the third round as he made three birdies at the front nine with only three bogeys coming at the second and seventh holeHe won by four shots from Njoroge Kibugu and Muthaiga professional Greg Snow who tied for second place on one under par 287 eachIt was a disastrous round for the 19-year-old Kibugu who picked up a seven on the stroke index one-seventh having earlier bogeyed the first, second, fourth and sixth